Sentencas: A Pd/MnO2 catalyst was used as the anode materials of an intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) for direct utilization of dimethylether (DME) gas fuel.
Titulo: Development of novel anodic catalyst for solid oxide fuel cell operated at intermediate-temperature direct utilizing of dimethylether fuel

Sentencas: The Pd/MnO, catalyst had morphology that nano Pd particles were dispersed on a manganese oxide with meso-scaled pores.
Titulo: Development of novel anodic catalyst for solid oxide fuel cell operated at intermediate-temperature direct utilizing of dimethylether fuel

Sentencas: A proton conducting oxide BaCe0.delta Y0.delta O3-delta was used as the electrolyte (thickness 500 pm) and a Pt was used as the cathode.
Titulo: Development of novel anodic catalyst for solid oxide fuel cell operated at intermediate-temperature direct utilizing of dimethylether fuel

Sentencas: The cell was operated at 600 degrees C. Maximum power density of the cell using Pt-Pd/MnO2 anode (Pd/MnO2 content of 16.6 wt.%) was 21 mW cm(-2) at 50 mA cm(-2), while the cells using Pt and Pd/MnO2 as anode materials exhibited maximum power densities of 9 and 10 MW cm(-2) at 20 mA cm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: Development of novel anodic catalyst for solid oxide fuel cell operated at intermediate-temperature direct utilizing of dimethylether fuel
